Dark Rituals</A><Br>Lanys T'vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 11:29:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grabs ankles and holds tightly..</span><hr size=1> Ah, but Verant believes the pre50 wizard class is balanced, and that wizard damage is balanced.   I think the numbers speak for themselves, but VI persists.  If I ever get out of 45 I might get to see these spells, but I'm in a small guild, so my chances of seeing a big raid are slim.  I must admit, I'd been hoping for something that would be of help to the rest of us...<br>
<br>
Caracatan Stormforge<br>
Devotee of Solusek Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uiudar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iudar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 12:50:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grabs ankles and holds tightly..</span><hr size=1> I'm resigned to slowly soloing until my friends twinks (they were just tired of their mains) are of a level they can group with me.<br>
<br>
<br>
Once that happens we are in business.  One is a cleric, one is an Enchanter, and the Guild has another wizard interested in AoE groups....<br>
<br>
<br>
2 slots to fill.  Puller and Stunner.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
With pickup groups I am still reduced to either Pity or Reputation to get me a group.<br>
<br>
I hate pity, and would probably quit a group if I found out that was the only reason I was let in...<br>
<br>
My reputation both as a player and a Wizard are excellent.  Reputation alone doesn't make up for the short comings of my class.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This enhancment <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a good thing.  The nightmare of a mob gating and summoning has been passed on to me by friends.  This certainly something that was needed at the end game.<br>
<br>
Still....   It is aimed more at Raid situations.  It will be of limited use for exp grouping (which VI doesn't seem to realze makes up the bulk of the player communties play time).<br>
<br>
It is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->something that will make every group leader go &quot;Hey!  I'm grabbing that Wizard that's LFG!&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
It's still just as hard as ever to level a Wizard up to 50+.  not because of some racial exp penalty, but because it's such a bitch to find a group after your mid-20s.<br>
<br>
<br>
They really need to find something to give those of us in our 30s.  The <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  real</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> problem with wizards is that, as has been pointed out, by the mid-late 30s we're tired of the bullshit.  Tired of LFG for hours on end, and not getting one until a friend logs on.  Friend doesn't log on you either work tradeskills, or play a twink.<br>
<br>
I'm tired with it.  I have played my monk heavily for the last several weeks.  I love playing a monk, but my heart is in the art of Wizardry.<br>
<br>
If something isn't done to help the middle aged wizards of the world (even if I'm 50+ at the time), I'll probably be gone when DAoC comes out.  The Hiberian Eldrich sounds like a major league badass...<br>
<br>
<br>
Wizards have been shafted repeatidly.  Misunderstood through out the process.  I'm quickly getting tired of it.<br>
<br>
<br>
I just hope my friends level up soon so we can start AoE groups.  The daily grind is getting old... <p><TABLE ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=460 COLS=1 BORDER=1 BGCOLOR=#FF0000>
